description:
Bug 3666: Code Completion - Hungry code assist (1GDRYW5)
Under certain circumstances, the code assist feature in the UI is eating too much code. When adding a parameter to the 'baz' call in the 'bar' method, the code assist should only replace until the cursor location or until the end of the current identifier. However, currently the code is being replaced until the end of the identifier.

Steps to reproduce:
1. Open the enclosed code sample.
2. Modify the 'baz' call in the 'bar' method to include a parameter.

After step 2, the code should be changed to:
baz(x.foo().foo())
I would rather it gave me:
baz(x.foo()x.foo())

public class X {
  void bar(X x) {
    baz(x.foo());
  }
  int foo() {
    return 5;
  }
  void baz(int i, int j) {}
}
